fields.description:
When I launch a lot of ebs backed instances simultaneously, and terminate them, sometimes the addresses and/or volumes are not released.  This issue was found debugging a quota issue.

Steps to reproduce.
1) Allocate qa machines (edge mode, 2 machines)
2) Create an account (account1)
3) Create 2 users (user1/user2)
4) Put the following quota on user1
{code}
{
  "Version":"2011-04-01",
  "Statement":[{
  "Sid":"4",
  "Effect":"Limit",
  "Action":"ec2:RunInstances",
   "Resource":"*",
   "Condition":{
     "NumericLessThanEquals": { "ec2:quota-vminstancenumber":"6" }
   }
   }]
}
{code}
5) Add a policy to user1 and user2 to allow them to do all ec2:* actions.
6) Generate credentials for user1 and user2.  Keep track of these keys
7) Load the qa image for Centos6
8) Run an instance of the Centos 6 image.
9) Create a 5GB volume, attach it to the instance.
10) Within the instance curl http://mirror.eucalyptus-systems.com/images/bfebs-image/lucid-bfebs-vmware-tools.img > <mounted volume>
11) Create a snapshot from the instance
12) Register the snapshot, remember the EBS instance ID.
13) Run the following java SDK
{code}
import com.amazonaws.auth.BasicAWSCredentials;
import com.amazonaws.services.ec2.AmazonEC2Client;
import com.amazonaws.services.ec2.model.RunInstancesRequest;

import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;
public class RunInstances2UsersTest {
  public static class RunInstanceThread extends Thread {
    public String imageId;
    public AmazonEC2Client ec2;
    public String EUCA_HOST = ""; // put EUCA_HOST_HERE
    public RunInstanceThread(String imageId, String accessKey, String secretKey) {
      this.imageId = imageId;
      BasicAWSCredentials EUCA_CREDS = new BasicAWSCredentials(accessKey, secretKey);
      this.ec2 = new AmazonEC2Client(EUCA_CREDS);
      ec2.setEndpoint("http://" + EUCA_HOST + "/services/compute/");
    }
    public void run() {
      RunInstancesRequest runInstancesRequest = new RunInstancesRequest();
      runInstancesRequest.setImageId(imageId);
      runInstancesRequest.setMinCount(1);
      runInstancesRequest.setMaxCount(1);
      System.out.println(ec2.runInstances(runInstancesRequest));
    }
  }

  public static void main(String [] args) {
    String IMAGE_ID = ""; // put image id here
    String USER_1_ACCESS_KEY = ""; // put user1 access key here
    String USER_1_SECRET_KEY = ""; // put user1 secret key here
    String USER_2_ACCESS_KEY = ""; // put user2 access key here
    String USER_2_SECRET_KEY = ""; // put user2 secret key here
    List<RunInstanceThread> runInstanceThreads = new ArrayList<RunInstanceThread>();
    for (int i=0;i<4;i++) {
      runInstanceThreads.add(new RunInstanceThread(IMAGE_ID,USER_1_ACCESS_KEY, USER_1_SECRET_KEY));
      runInstanceThreads.add(new RunInstanceThread(IMAGE_ID,USER_2_ACCESS_KEY, USER_2_SECRET_KEY));
    }
    for (RunInstanceThread runInstanceThread: runInstanceThreads) {
      runInstanceThread.start();
    }
  }
}
{code}

14) from euca2ools as user user1, run 
{code}
for i in $(euca-describe-instances | grep "i-" | sed "s/^.*\ti-/i-/g" | sed "s/\t.*$//g"); do euca-terminate-instances $i; done
{code}

until you see no instances remaining in euca-describe-instances.

Repeat steps 13 and 14 until you see something like this:
{code}
Exception in thread "Thread-8" com.amazonaws.AmazonServiceException: Not enough resources available: addresses; please stop or terminate unwanted instances or release unassociated elastic IPs and try again, or run with private addressing only (Service: AmazonEC2; Status Code: 500; Error Code: InsufficientInstanceCapacity; Request ID: bda302c5-b641-4944-8d4a-18c2d44bdd6a)
	at com.amazonaws.http.AmazonHttpClient.handleErrorResponse(AmazonHttpClient.java:1032)
	at com.amazonaws.http.AmazonHttpClient.executeOneRequest(AmazonHttpClient.java:687)
	at com.amazonaws.http.AmazonHttpClient.executeHelper(AmazonHttpClient.java:441)
	at com.amazonaws.http.AmazonHttpClient.execute(AmazonHttpClient.java:292)
	at com.amazonaws.services.ec2.AmazonEC2Client.invoke(AmazonEC2Client.java:9225)
	at com.amazonaws.services.ec2.AmazonEC2Client.runInstances(AmazonEC2Client.java:4382)
	at .RunInstances2UsersTest$RunInstanceThread.run(RunInstances2Test.java:36)
{code}

Addresses have not been released, even though they should have been during the euca-terminate-instances

euca-describe-addresses verbose from the eucalyptus account may show something like this:

{code}
